%% Diagram: Signed Double-Submit CSRF Token Flow
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser
    participant Server

    Note over Server: secret = HMAC key (server-only)
    Browser->>Server: GET /app (authenticated session)
    Note over Server: rand = randomBytes(16)<br/>token = HMAC(secret, sessionID + rand) + "." + rand
    Server-->>Browser: 200 OK<br/>Set-Cookie __Host-csrf=token Secure HttpOnly SameSite=Strict Path=/<br/>HTML embeds same token in form or meta tag

    Note over Browser: User submits the form, or JS reads token<br/>from meta and sets X-CSRF-Token header

    Browser->>Server: POST /transfer<br/>Cookie __Host-csrf=token<br/>X-CSRF-Token token<br/>Body ...

    Note over Server: 1. cookie == header (constant-time compare)<br/>2. split header into hmac and rand<br/>3. recompute HMAC(secret, sessionID + rand)<br/>4. constant-time compare with submitted hmac
    alt Both checks pass
        Server-->>Browser: 200 OK
    else Mismatch or tamper
        Server-->>Browser: 403 Forbidden + log security event
    end
